==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prangos
<hw>Pran"gos</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[From the
native name in <country>Afghanistan</country>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of umbelliferous plants, one species of which (<spn>Prangos
pabularia</spn>), found in <geog>Tibet</geog>, <geog>Cashmere</geog>,
<country>Afghanistan</country>, etc., has been used as fodder for
cattle. It has decompound leaves with very long narrow divisions, and a
highly fragrant smell resembling that of new clover hay.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prank</ent>⟦br⟧
